<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Overland (time) travel. I'm not sure if this is technically a bug, but it seems like movement on the world map occurs really quickly in comparison to time passing (in-game, measured per ctrl-T). For example, one can move on the world map from Bree up to Angband in under an hour game-time, yet of course you can go from full to starving. <p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Only one-tenth the time passes.  This is a deliberate optimization, because otherwise overland travel would be really slow on old computers. 
</p>
<p>
I guess we can leave it a bug, though, to find a way to optimize it with less in-game impact.  Some modules might use the calendar more, after all. 
</p>
